Titolo: Lexi-Cross

Anno: 1991

Descrizione: Lexi-Cross is a video game written by Peter Oliphant for MS-DOS and published by Interplay Productions in 1991. A Macintosh version was released in 1992. Lexi-Cross presents a futuristic TV game show, with elements similar to Wheel of Fortune, Scrabble, and Battleship. Players can choose to play as human or alien, and computer opponents are robots.
The game came with a small booklet parodying the format and style of TV Guide that served as a game manual and copy protection device.

Genere: Word 

Valutazione: N/A
